Let $X$ denote the diameter of an armored electric cable and $Y$ denote the diameter of the ceramic mold that makes the cable. Both $X$ and $Y$ are scaled so that they range between 0 and 1. Suppose that $X$ and $Y$ have the joint density function given by:

\[
f(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
\frac{1}{y}, & 0 < x < y < 1 \\
0, & \text{elsewhere}
\end{cases}
\]

Find the probability $P(X+Y > 1/2)$. Provide your answer to four decimal places.

Evaluate the sum \( \sum_{n=-\infty}^\infty f(n) \), where for any integer \( n \), \( k(n) = \frac{n^7}{7} + \frac{n^3}{3} + \frac{11n}{21} + 1 \) and
\[
f(n) = \begin{cases}
0 & \text{if } k(n) \text{ is an integer} \\
\frac{1}{n^2} & \text{if } k(n) \text{ is not an integer}
\end{cases}
\]

Compute the value of the double integral \( \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} f(x,y) \, dx \, dy \), where the function \( f(x,y) \) is defined as follows:
\[
f(x,y) =
\begin{cases}
 g(x)/x,&\text{if}\, 0 < y < x\\
 0, &\text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
and \( g(x) \) is a non-negative function defined on \((0, \infty)\) with \( \int_{0}^{\infty} g(x) \, dx = 1 \).

Given the joint probability density function for random variables $X$ and $Y$:
\[ f(x, y)=\begin{cases}
2(x+y)  & \text{if } 0<x<y<1 \\
0 &  \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}. \]
Find the real number $a$ such that the conditional expectation $E(X | Y=aX)=\frac{2}{9}$. \(a\) is a real number.

Evaluate the integral \( \frac{\pi^2}{10} \int_{-10}^{10} f(x) \cos{\pi x} \, dx \), where \( f(x) \) is defined on the interval \([-10,10]\) by
\[
f(x)=
\begin{cases}
x-\lfloor{x}\rfloor & \text{if} \ \lfloor{x}\rfloor \text{ is odd} \\
1+\lfloor{x}\rfloor-x & \text{if} \ \lfloor{x}\rfloor \text{ is even}
\end{cases}
\]

Use the Chinese Remainder Theorem to solve the following system of congruences:
\[\begin{cases}
x \equiv 1 \pmod{4} \\
x \equiv -1 \pmod{25}
\end{cases}\]
Find the value of \( x \) modulo 100.

